ng-app.doc: Use this directive to auto-bootstrap an application. Only one ngApp directive can be used per HTML document. The directive designates the root of the application and is typically placed at the root of the page.

ng-bind.doc: Replaces the text content of the specified HTML element with the value of a given expression, and to update the text content when the value of that expression changes.

ng-bind-html.doc: Creates a binding that will innerHTML the result of evaluating the expression into the current element in a secure way.

ng-bind-html-unsafe.doc: Same as ng-bind-html, but without control on the inserted html content.

ng-change.doc:
Evaluates given expression when user changes the input.

<input ng-change="{expression}"/>

ng-checked.doc:
Expression evaluated when the input is checked/unchecked.

<input ng-checked="{expression}"/>

ng-class.doc:
Sets CSS classes on HTML an element dynamically.

<any ng-class="{ btn: true, btn-active: isActive(user) }">...</any>

ng-click.doc: Allows you to specify custom behavior when element is clicked.

ng-dblclick.doc: Specifies custom behavior on dblclick event.

ng-cloak.doc: Used to prevent the Angular html template from being briefly displayed by the browser in its uncompiled form while your application is loading.

ng-controller.doc: Links a part of the HTML DOM to a controller.

ng-if.doc:
Removes and/or recreates a portion of the DOM tree conditionally.

<span ng-if="checked">Checkbox is checked.</span>
